{{Quote|My Lord dreams in darkness and I wait&mdash;as did my mother before me, and her father before her.|Darth Wyyrlok (III)|<ref name="Legacy 14" />}}
'''Darth Wyyrlok''' was a [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Chagrian/Legends|Chagrian]] who served the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth Krayt]] as a [[Sith Master/Legends|Sith Master]]. She became Krayt's closest advisor sometime after [[41 ABY]], following in the footsteps of her [[Parent/Legends|father]], who had also been called [[Darth Wyyrlok (I)|Darth Wyyrlok]]. She additionally acted as Krayt's [[voice]] and the [[Regent/Legends|Regent]] of his [[One Sith|Sith order]] while he rested in [[Suspended animation/Legends|stasis]]. Wyyrlok eventually mothered a [[Darth Wyyrlok (III)|son]], who assumed her name and duties before [[130 ABY]].

==Biography==
{{Quote|For three generations, my family has served you, Lord Krayt.|Darth Wyyrlok (III)|<ref name="Legacy 30">[[Legacy (2006) 30|''Legacy'' (2006) 30]]</ref>}}
The [[Gender/Legends|female]]<ref name="Legacy 14" /> [[Chagrian/Legends|Chagrian]]<ref name="Legacy 0" /> [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Wyyrlok served the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth Krayt]] as a [[Sith Master/Legends|Sith Master]] of his [[One Sith]] order.<ref name="Legacy 0.5">[[Star Wars: Legacy (2006) 0½|''Star Wars: Legacy'' (2006) 0½]]</ref> Her [[Parent/Legends|father]] was also called [[Darth Wyyrlok (I)|Darth Wyyrlok]]<ref name="Legacy 0" /> and was Krayt's top [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]] and closest advisor<ref name="Legacy 14" /> as early as [[41 ABY]].<ref name="CrosscurrentDate">''[[Crosscurrent]]'', in which [[Darth Wyyrlok (I)|Darth Wyyrlok]] is [[Darth Krayt]]'s closest advisor, is set in [[41 ABY]] according to ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''.</ref> His duties were eventually passed down to his daughter, who became Krayt's most trusted advisor and acted as the guardian of the One [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] while her Master rested in [[Suspended animation/Legends|stasis]].<ref name="Legacy 31">[[Legacy (2006) 31|''Legacy'' (2006) 31]]</ref> The Sith remained hidden on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]] for a century, and as Krayt's order and his plans to conquer [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] developed and grew,<ref name="Legacy 0" /> he often retired to stasis for [[Standard year/Legends|years]] at a time.<ref name="Legacy 18">[[Legacy (2006) 18|''Legacy'' (2006) 18]]</ref> Like her father before her, Wyyrlok became Krayt's [[voice]] and the [[Regent/Legends|regent]] of the One Sith during these periods.<ref name="Legacy 34">[[Legacy (2006) 34|''Legacy'' (2006) 34]]</ref> She had a [[Darth Wyyrlok (III)|son]] at some point, and after she passed away he assumed her name and responsibilities.<ref name="Legacy 0" /> The third Darth Wyyrlok was serving Darth Krayt by [[130 ABY]] when Krayt [[Attack on Emperor Fel|seized]] control of the galaxy.<ref name="Legacy 1">[[Legacy (2006) 1|''Legacy'' (2006) 1]]</ref>

==Personality and traits==
The Sith had [[Color/Legends|red]] skin with black [[tattoo]]s.<ref name="Legacy War 1" /> She was loyal to Darth Krayt and waited for his commands.<ref name="Legacy 14" />

==Powers and abilities==
{{Quote|I will again assume the duties all Wyyrlok have held while our master rests in stasis&mdash;as the voice of our Lord Krayt and Regent of the Sith order.|Darth Wyyrlok (III)|<ref name="Legacy 34" />}}
Darth Wyyrlok was a Sith Master of the One Sith,<ref name="Legacy 14" /> an organization of [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-users]] deeply immersed in the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]].<ref name="Legacy 0" /> Darth Krayt placed great faith in her ability to lead the Sith in his absence, appointing her as his voice and the regent of the order while he rested in stasis.<ref name="Legacy 34" />

==Equipment==
Darth Wyyrlok wore a black [[Armor/Legends|armor]] with [[Metal/Legends|metallic]] plates.<ref name="Legacy War 1" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|To your other question&mdash;yes, I do sometimes consult with other artists when projects or aliens or characters overlap. For instance, Doug Wheatley and I put out ''[sic]'' drawing brains together on creating a good look for a Chagrian female when he was drawing Chagrians in Dark Times and I was drawing Wyyrlok's daughter in Legacy.|Jan Duursema|<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=posts/30637140|board=Authors and Artists|thread=The Official Jan Duursema Discussion Thread|user=[[Jan Duursema|Jan_Duursema]]|date=2009-09-29|time=6:22 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907193625/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-official-jan-duursema-discussion-thread.5915607/page-95|quote=[&hellip;] Doug Wheatley and I put out drawing brains together on creating a good look for a Chagrian female when he was drawing Chagrians in Dark Times and I was drawing Wyyrlok's daughter in Legacy.}}</ref>}}
Darth Wyyrlok was created by [[John Ostrander]] and [[Jan Duursema]], the authors of the [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] series ''[[Star Wars: Legacy]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: Legacy — War]]''. She was first indirectly mentioned in the preview comic [[Star Wars: Legacy (2006) 0|''Star Wars: Legacy'' (2006) 0]],<ref name="Legacy 0" />  published on [[June 7]], [[2006]],<ref name="DarkHorse">{{DarkHorse|url=Comics/13-514/Star-Wars-Legacy-0|text=STAR WARS: LEGACY #0}}</ref> which noted that her son was the third Sith to take the name Darth Wyyrlok.<ref name="Legacy 0" /> She first appeared in a flashback scene in the [[Legacy — War 1|first issue]] of ''Legacy''{{'s}} followup miniseries, ''Star Wars: Legacy—War'', illustrated by [[Jan Duursema]]<ref name="Legacy War 1" /> and published on [[December 15]], [[2010]].<ref name="Marvel">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/54441/star_wars_legacy_-_war_2010_1|text=Star Wars: Legacy - War (2010) #1}}</ref> While designing the character's look, Duursema consulted with fellow artist [[Douglas Wheatley]], who was also penciling female Chagrian characters for the comic series ''[[Star Wars: Dark Times]]''.<ref name="JCF" />

